@nareshgbhat - the phrase `retest this please` is meant for the automated test framework to re-run the unit tests on a pull request. 

When I made that comment, it triggered the unit tests to re-run. If they succeed, then we can submit this PR.
@jonathan-hurley and when you repeated the same phrase to explain its meaning, it triggered another re-run. ;)

@nitirajrathore components in `contrib` are not built/tested by the Jenkins jobs, so neither failure nor success are indicative of the change.  I would say that until this oversight in the build system is addressed, you can go ahead and merge once you have enough approving reviews.

Also, to avoid making Jenkins perform unnecessary builds, please include `[skip ci]` in the pull request text.

> LGTM. One question though: are most/all other Python scripts in Ambari compatible with Python 3?

I have not investigated what it would take to get everything to Py3 compatibility. This script sticks out because it prevents users from running PySpark jobs on Python 3.x, regardless of what Python is running Ambari itself.
